text:
The Bay Area has broken the previous record for the most Spare the Air alerts issued in a year — and new records will continue to be set, as the air district extended an alert to Tuesday.

https://t.co/WTRJF1h10H

“The complete, willful nonchalance about the hazard he is imposing on his fellow human beings that we’ve seen in his approach to the epidemic is now being demonstrated in his personal behavior,” said Dr. Steven Goodman, a Stanford epidemiologist.

name: sfchronicle
text:
JUST IN: President Trump’s physician said in a statement Saturday that "he is no longer considered a transmission risk to others.” 

The statement does not say when Trump’s last negative test was, or whether he is still testing positive. https://t.co/px1C9Dvvdi
